title: Problem with installing DLC-CPU environment "CondaEnvException: Pip failed"
body:
Hello! I am new to DeepLabCut & I am struggling with installing the DLC-CPU environment. I would really appreciate if someone can help me out. (MacBook Air, macOS 10.15.5. Python 3.7.6. Using the most recent version of Anaconda.) **Describe the problem** Every time I try to create an environment using the CPU yaml file, I get a message "CondaEnvException: Pip failed." I thought that anaconda was somehow installed weirdly, so I tried deleting it and downloading anaconda over and over (tried both cmd installer and the graphic installer to download it). However, it didn't solve the issue and I still get the exception no matter what.
